      "rationale": "Model form selection is documented with explicit justification: RANS k-ω SST turbulence model selected based on published benchmarking studies for rotating blood pump flows (Hariharan et al. 2011, Fraser et al. 2012). Power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen et al. 1990, modified Heuser-Opitz) selected based on comparative study of five hemolysis models against the bench dataset. Model form uncertainty estimated via the model comparison study: NIH predictions span ±18% across the five hemolysis models; the selected model achieves the lowest systematic bias (< 3%) against bench data.",
